---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const description =
  'Fractional CTO for companies navigating AI adoption, architecture strategy, and high-stakes technology decisions. I work with 2–3 companies at a time.';

const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ProfessionalService',
  name: 'Simon Plant — Fractional CTO',
  url: new URL('/services', Astro.site).href,
  description,
  founder: { '@type': 'Person', name: 'Simon Plant' },
  areaServed: 'Remote / Los Angeles',
};
---

<Base title="Services — Simon Plant" description={description} jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <main class="section-spacing">
    <div class="prose">
      <h1>Fractional CTO</h1>

      <p>
        I work with 2–3 companies at a time on AI strategy, enterprise architecture, and the technology decisions that determine whether you scale or stall. Thirty years of pattern recognition — web hosting in 1994, enterprise cloud in 2008, DevOps in 2014, AI agents now — applied to your specific situation.
      </p>

      <h2>What I do</h2>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>AI reality checks.</strong> Cutting through the hype to find where AI actually moves the needle for your business — and protecting data privacy and IP while you do it. I run AI agents in production myself; the advice comes from operating the technology, not reading about it.</li>
        <li><strong>Architecture strategy.</strong> Spotting the "small" decisions that become "large" technical debt. I've watched this movie enough times to recognize the pattern early — and to know which corners are safe to cut.</li>
        <li><strong>Executive advisory.</strong> Build-vs-buy, vendor selection, team structure — the decisions where thirty years of context on what works and what doesn't is worth more than another meeting.</li>
        <li><strong>Initiative design and delivery.</strong> Turning a strategic bet into an executable plan — target architecture, sequencing, team shape — and staying engaged with the program team through delivery, not just the kickoff deck.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How I work</h2>

      <p>
        Fractional means senior attention without the full-time cost: a standing engagement, not a one-off report. Half the work is advisory — with leadership on strategy, with program teams on delivery. The other half is hands-on: I can code-review a Python data application in the morning and present AI strategy to your Board in the afternoon. Based in Los Angeles, working remotely. CISSP.
      </p>

      <h2>Is this you?</h2>

      <p>
        You're working through a technology decision where the cost of getting it wrong is high — AI adoption, architecture strategy, build-vs-buy, team structure. You want someone who has operated at enterprise scale and still ships code. That's the conversation I want to have.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a href="mailto:website@simonplant.com">website@simonplant.com</a> &middot;
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/simonplant" rel="me">LinkedIn</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
</Base>
